<topic xml:id="ha-resources-deleting"
 role="task" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <info>
    <title>Deleting cluster resources</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="tahlia.richardson@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>
        You can delete a cluster resource with the &crmshell; (&crmsh;) or with &hawk;. !!You don't need to stop the resource first when using Hawk!!
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>

  <itemizedlist>
    <title>Requirements</title>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        The resource has been cleaned up, if needed.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

  <variablelist role="tabs">
    <varlistentry>
      <term>&crmshell;</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can perform this procedure on any node in the cluster.
        </para>
        <procedure>
          <step>
            <para>
              Log in either as the &rootuser; user or as a user with <command>sudo</command>
              privileges.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Check the current status of the resource:
            </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo crm resource status</command></screen>
            <para>
              If the resource is already <literal>Stopped</literal>, you can skip to
              <xref linkend="ha-resources-removing-crmsh-delete"/>.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              If the resource is <literal>Started</literal>, you can stop it with the following
              command:
            </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo crm resource stop <replaceable>RESOURCE</replaceable></command></screen>
            <para>
              You can also stop multiple resources at once:
              </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo crm resource stop <replaceable>RESOURCE1</replaceable> <replaceable>RESOURCE2</replaceable></command></screen>
          </step>
          <step xml:id="ha-resources-removing-crmsh-delete">
            <para>
              Delete the resource:
            </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo crm configure delete <replaceable>RESOURCE</replaceable></command></screen>
            <para>
              You can also delete multiple resources at once:
              </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo crm configure delete <replaceable>RESOURCE1</replaceable> <replaceable>RESOURCE2</replaceable></command></screen>
          </step>
        </procedure>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>&hawk;</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can access the &hawk; Web interface from any machine that has network access to
          the nodes.
        </para>
        <procedure>
          <step>
            <para>
              In a Web browser, go to
              <literal>https://<replaceable>HAWKSERVER</replaceable>:7630/</literal>
              and log in.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              From the left navigation bar, select <menuchoice><guimenu>Monitoring</guimenu>
              <guimenu>Status</guimenu></menuchoice>.
            </para>
            <para>
              The <guimenu>Resources</guimenu> tab shows the <guimenu>Status</guimenu> of the
              cluster resources. If the resource you want to delete has a red <guimenu>Status</guimenu>
              icon, you can skip to <xref linkend="ha-resources-removing-hawk-delete"/>.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              If the resource you want to delete has a green <guimenu>Status</guimenu> icon, go to
              its <guimenu>Operations</guimenu> column and click the <guimenu>Stop</guimenu> button.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Click <guimenu>OK</guimenu> to continue.
            </para>
            <para>
              The resource's <guimenu>Status</guimenu> icon changes to red.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step xml:id="ha-resources-removing-hawk-delete">
            <para>
              From the left navigation bar, select <menuchoice><guimenu>Configuration</guimenu>
              <guimenu>Edit Configuration</guimenu></menuchoice>.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              In the <guimenu>Resources</guimenu> tab, find the resource you want to delete. In its
              <guimenu>Operations</guimenu> column, click the <guimenu>Delete</guimenu> button.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Click <guimenu>OK</guimenu> to continue.
            </para>
            <para>
              A message at the top of the screen shows if the action was successful.
            </para>
          </step>
        </procedure>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</topic>
